'''Gight''' is the name of an estate in the parish of [[Fyvie]] in the [[Formartine]] area of [[Aberdeenshire]], [[Scotland]], [[United Kingdom]]. It is best known as the location of the 16th-century '''Gight Castle''',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://hsewsf.sedsh.gov.uk/hslive/hsstart?P_HBNUM=9628 |title=Gight Castle: Listed Building Report |publisher=Historic Scotland}}</ref> ancestral home of [[Lord Byron]]. The Gight Woods are presently a protected natural forest.<ref>[http://www.aboutaberdeen.com/gightcastle.php Gight Castle River Ythan Methlick Aberdeenshire]. AboutAberdeen.com. Accessed March 20, 2012.</ref>

